net.hudup.core.evaluate.recommend

Class Accuracy

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.hudup.core.alg.AlgAbstract
      • net.hudup.core.evaluate.MetricAbstract
        • net.hudup.core.evaluate.DefaultMetric
          • net.hudup.core.evaluate.recommend.Accuracy
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.rmi.Remote, java.util.EventListener, Alg, AlgRemote, SetupAlgListener, Exportable, Metric, MetricRemote
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ClassificationAccuracy, CorrelationAccuracy, PredictiveAccuracy

    public abstract class Accuracy
extends DefaultMetric
    Currently, two default metrics inherited from DefaultMetric class are TimeMetric class and Accuracy class. TimeMetric measures the speed of algorithm and so it is the time in seconds that methods RecommenderRemote.estimate(net.hudup.core.alg.RecommendParam, Set) and RecommenderRemote.recommend(net.hudup.core.alg.RecommendParam, int) execute over Dataset. Accuracy reflects goodness and efficiency of recommendation algorithms. There are three types of accuracy.
    • Predictive accuracy, represented by PredictiveAccuracy class, measures how close predicted ratings returned from methods RecommenderRemote.estimate(net.hudup.core.alg.RecommendParam, Set) and RecommenderRemote.recommend(net.hudup.core.alg.RecommendParam, int) are to the true user ratings. PredictiveAccuracy class derives directly from Accuracy class. MAE, MSE, RMSE are typical predictive accuracy metrics.
    • Classification accuracy, represented by ClassificationAccuracy class, measures the frequency that methods RecommenderRemote.estimate(net.hudup.core.alg.RecommendParam, Set) and RecommenderRemote.recommend(net.hudup.core.alg.RecommendParam, int) make correct or incorrect recommendation. ClassificationAccuracy class derives directly from Accuracy class. Precision and Recall are typical classification accuracy metrics.
    • Correlation accuracy, represented by CorrelationAccuracy class, measures the ability that method RecommenderRemote.recommend(net.hudup.core.alg.RecommendParam, int) makes the ordering of recommended items which is similar to the ordering of user's favorite items. CorrelationAccuracy class derives directly from Accuracy class. NDPM, Spearman, Pearson are typical correlation accuracy metrics.

      • calc

        protected abstract MetricValue calc(RatingVector recommended,
                                    RatingVector vTesting,
                                    Dataset testing)
        Calculating metric value at a iteration of algorithm execution. The calculation is based on comparing recommended rating vector and testing rating vector. Because this is abstract method, all classes inherits from Accuracy must implement it.
        Parameters:
        recommended - list of recommended items known as recommended rating vector which is produced by recommendation process.
        vTesting - the testing rating vector which is used to compare with recommended rating vector.
        testing - testing dataset where the testing rating vector is extracted.
        Returns:
        MetricValue at a iteration of algorithm execution.
